name: Simba Hodari
description: Simba Hodari is a brave and playful cat from Kilimani. He loves basking in the sun and watching birds in the garden. His friendly nature makes him a perfect companion for families in the bustling neighborhoods of Nairobi.

name: Malaika
description: Malaika, meaning 'angel' in Swahili, is an elegant cat from the coastal region. She has the distinctive wild-looking coat of the Sokoke breed and moves with natural grace. She loves spending time on high perches, watching life go by in her Mombasa neighborhood.

name: Zawadi
description: Zawadi, meaning 'gift' in Swahili, is a gentle soul from Karen. She enjoys the peaceful atmosphere of garden estates and has a particular fondness for afternoon tea time with her family.

name: Baraka
description: Baraka, meaning 'blessing' in Swahili, is a majestic cat from Lamu. With his distinctive coat pattern and friendly personality, he brings joy to everyone he meets. He loves exploring the historic streets of his island home.

name: Imani
description: Imani, meaning 'faith' in Swahili, is a spirited young cat from Westlands. She loves climbing the acacia trees in her garden and watching the sunset over the Nairobi skyline.

name: Tumaini
description: Tumaini, meaning 'hope' in Swahili, is a wise and gentle cat from Malindi. His curious nature leads him to explore the coastal gardens, always returning home with interesting stories to tell through his expressive eyes.

name: Nyota
description: Nyota, meaning 'star' in Swahili, is a mysterious beauty from Lavington. Her piercing eyes seem to hold ancient wisdom, and she moves with the grace of a traditional dancer. Though reserved at first, she forms deep bonds with her family.

name: Furaha
description: Furaha, meaning 'joy' in Swahili, is a cheerful cat from Diani Beach. He loves the sound of ocean waves and playing in the warm coastal breeze. His friendly nature makes him a favorite among beach-going families.

name: Jabari
description: Jabari, meaning 'brave one' in Swahili, is a strong and confident cat from Muthaiga. He has a commanding presence that matches his name, yet he's gentle with children and loves lounging in the shade of indigenous trees.
